title: 'B620 follow-up: Coq extracted AgentLoop integrity path doesn''t drop empty assistants'
---
cx-reviewer follow-up on B620 round 3: while native Message_history.ensure_tool_group_integrity now correctly drops empty assistant messages (preserving Codex replay state), the Coq-extracted equivalent at src/extracted/clawq_core.ml:835 only strips orphan calls/results — it doesn't drop empty assistant messages or preserve provider_response_items_json/thinking.

Affected callers: Agent.trim_history and Agent.force_compress_history at src/agent_0_compact.ml:230 still route through Clawq_core.AgentLoop.ensure_tool_group_integrity (extracted), not the native version. After trim_history, an all-orphan assistant remains in agent.history, which causes the same Anthropic 400 'tool call result does not follow tool call' or 'text content blocks must be non-empty' failures.

Conformance oracle: src/agent_loop_conformance.ml verifies native vs extracted match — divergence will eventually surface there.

Fix options:
1. Route trim/compress sanitization through native Message_history.ensure_tool_group_integrity instead of the extracted Coq function. Simplest.
2. Extend the Coq AgentLoop message model to represent provider items + thinking + empty-message predicate. Larger Coq change.

Add tests through Agent.trim_history / force_compress_history (not direct Message_history) to cover the broken path.

Tag: coq, message-history, anthropic-api